{"ts":"2026-06-17T15:59:46.213Z","author":"claude-code-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"Scope: resolveEventEndAt + the relative-offset parser. Keep --deadline/relative-token semantics (m=months) unchanged for backward compat; introduce a distinct minutes token only for durations, or accept ISO-8601 duration. Update docs + completions. 100% cov."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-zoe4"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Sub-hour duration granularity for scheduling: support minutes in --duration / event duration="},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"The relative-time parser (RELATIVE_DEADLINE) supports h/d/w/m where m=MONTHS; there is no minutes unit, so 'pm meet --duration 30m' resolves to +30 months and sub-hour meetings can only be expressed via an explicit --end ISO. Add a minutes-capable duration form (e.g. accept '30min' or ISO-8601 PT30M) in resolveEventEndAt's duration path, shared by pm create --event duration= and the pm meet/event shortcuts. Surfaced while implementing GH-217 (pm-76r5)."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Feature"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":4},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","backlog","scheduling"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-17T15:59:46.213Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-17T15:59:46.213Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"claude-code-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-mpbb"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"14547693bc3f449ca5bd9288e77cc5658d66348c81d8eae4f45b20f15a8dae03","message":""}
